---
export const prerender = true;
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';

import Main from '../layouts/main.astro';
import ClickToCopyEmail from '../components/click-to-copy-email';
import CtaExternal from '../components/cta-external.astro';
---

<Main
  fullWidth={true}
  title='Independent Advocate'
  description='Independent Product and Developer Advocacy'
  slug='/independent-advocate/'
  image='https://paulie.dev/images/ia-open-graph-image.jpg'
>
  <div class='mt-16 mb-32'>
    <strong class='block text-center xl:text-2xl text-brand-primary'>Paul Scanlon</strong>
    <h1 class='my-6 text-4xl xl:text-7xl text-center'>Independent Advocate</h1>
    <p class='text-center xl:text-2xl mx-auto xl:max-w-xl'>
      Hi, I'm Paul. I act <span class='text-brand-tertiary'>independently</span> to create content that drives awareness
      of products, features and services.
    </p>
    <small class='block xl:text-lg text-center mx-auto max-w-lg'>
      On this page you'll find information about my approach to Product Marketing, Developer Advocacy... and a
      <i>little something</i> I like to call <span class='text-brand-tertiary'>Bundles</span>.
    </small>
    <div class='flex justify-center py-8'>
      <ClickToCopyEmail />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class='flex flex-col gap-16 xl:gap-48'>
    <div class='grid items-center xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <Image
        width='984'
        height='554'
        alt='About me'
        src='/images/ia-about-me.png'
        class='xl:order-2 m-0 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
      />
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl'>About Me</h2>
        <p>
          I've held various positions in and around Advertising, Tech and Product Development in both full-time, and
          freelance positions since <span class='text-brand-primary'>2005</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I sit somewhere between Product Marketing and Developer Advocacy. I specialize in the creation of technical
          content for <span class='text-brand-secondary'>educational</span> and <span class='text-brand-tertiary'
            >promotional</span
          > purposes.
        </p>
        <p>You can read more about me on the <a href='/about/'>About</a> page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='grid items-center xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div class='order-2'>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl'>It's Not About Me!</h2>
        <p>I'm not a tech influencer and I'm not interested in building my own online brand.</p>
        <p>
          I'm passionate about technology and I liked being an <i>Engineer</i> but, what I really <b>LOVE</b> to do is: <span
            class='text-brand-primary'>design</span
          >, <span class='text-brand-secondary'>develop</span>{' '}
          <b>and</b>
          {' '}<span class='text-brand-tertiary'>write</span>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <Image
        width='984'
        height='554'
        alt='Not About me'
        src='/images/ia-not-about-me.png'
        class='m-0 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
      />
    </div>

    <div class='border border-brand-outline bg-brand-surface p-8 xl:p-16'>
      <h2 class='mt-0 mb-4 text-4xl xl:text-6xl text-center'>Bundles</h2>
      <p class='text-center mx-auto max-w-3xl'>
        Usually it takes a team to create go to market assets, but since I'm <b>multi-disciplined</b>, I'm able to take
        your marketing message and bring it to life using a number of different techniques.
      </p>
      <p class='text-center mx-auto max-w-4xl'>
        Bundles consist of, but are
        <b>not</b> limited to:
      </p>
      <ol class='xl:flex xl:gap-16 justify-center xl:text-lg xl:font-bold'>
        <li class='m-0 p-0'>Written Content</li>
        <li class='m-0 p-0'>Demo site / application</li>
        <li class='m-0 p-0'>Open-source GitHub repository</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class='grid gap-0 xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl' id='extra-small-bundle'>
          <a class='no-underline font-black text-brand-salmon' href='#extra-small-bundle'>Extra Small Bundle</a>
        </h2>

        <Image
          width='984'
          height='554'
          alt='Extra Small Bundle'
          src='/images/ia-xs-bundle.jpg'
          class='mt-0 mb-8 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
        />
        <p>Written content with code snippets as part of the article or post.</p>
        <p>Content can be published on either your company blog, or by a suitable external publisher.</p>
      </div>
      <div class='xl:order-2 pt-0 xl:pt-12'>
        <dl>
          <dt>Smashing Magazine</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2023/09/getting-started-with-neon-branching/'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>Getting Started With Neon Branching</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='grid gap-0 xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl' id='small-bundle'>
          <a class='no-underline font-black text-brand-salmon' href='#small-bundle'>Small Bundle</a>
        </h2>
        <Image
          width='984'
          height='554'
          alt='Small Bundle'
          src='/images/ia-sm-bundle.jpg'
          class='mt-0 mb-8 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
        />
        <p>Written content with sample code publicly available on GitHub.</p>
        <p>Content can be published on either, your company blog, or by a suitable external publisher.</p>
      </div>
      <div class='xl:order-2 pt-0 xl:pt-12'>
        <dl>
          <dt>Neon Blog</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://neon.tech/blog/roll-your-own-analytics-with-astro-vercel-edge-functions-and-neon'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>Roll Your Own Analytics With Astro, Vercel Edge Functions and Neon</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Open-source Repository</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://github.com/PaulieScanlon/neon-edge-analytics-astro-sample' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://github.com/PaulieScanlon/neon-edge-analytics-astro-sample</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='grid gap-0 xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl' id='medium-bundle'>
          <a class='no-underline font-black text-brand-salmon' href='#medium-bundle'>Medium Bundle</a>
        </h2>
        <Image
          width='984'
          height='554'
          alt='Medium Bundle'
          src='/images/ia-md-bundle.jpg'
          class='mt-0 mb-8 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
        />
        <p>
          Written content with production code publicly available on GitHub and a demo site/application deployed to <span
            class='text-brand-tertiary'>your domain</span
          >.
        </p>
        <p>Content can be published on either, your company blog, or by a suitable external publisher.</p>
        <small
          >Case study: <a href='/demos/2023/09/how-to-use-postgres-at-the-edge/'>How to use Postgres at the Edge</a
          ></small
        >
      </div>
      <div class='xl:order-2 pt-0 xl:pt-12'>
        <dl>
          <dt>Neon Blog</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://neon.tech/blog/how-to-use-postgres-at-the-edge' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >How to use Postgres at the Edge</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Open-source Repository</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://github.com/neondatabase/ping-thing' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://github.com/neondatabase/ping-thing</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Social Assets</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://x.com/neondatabase/status/1704544628060365203?s=20' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://x.com/neondatabase/status/1704544628060365203?s=20</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dd class='not-prose !list-none'>
            <CtaExternal href='https://neon.tech/demos/ping-thing' className='!justify-start my-8'>
              Visit Demo
            </CtaExternal>
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='grid gap-0 xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl' id='large-bundle'>
          <a class='no-underline font-black text-brand-salmon' href='#large-bundle'>Large Bundle</a>
        </h2>
        <Image
          width='984'
          height='554'
          alt='Large Bundle'
          src='/images/ia-lg-bundle.jpg'
          class='mt-0 mb-8 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
        />
        <p>
          Written content with production code publicly available on GitHub and a demo site/application deployed to <span
            class='text-brand-tertiary'>your domain</span
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          Content can be published on either, your company blog, or by a suitable external publisher, with additional
          supporting content that mentions, and links back to other assets from the Bundle.
        </p>
        <small>Case study: <a href='/demos/2023/04/cockroachdb-cloud-api/'>What Is the CockroachDB Cloud API</a></small>
      </div>
      <div class='xl:order-2 pt-0 xl:pt-12'>
        <dl>
          <dt>Cockroach Labs Blog</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://www.cockroachlabs.com/blog/what-is-the-cockroachdb-cloud-api/'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>What is the CockroachDB Cloud API and why should you use It?</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Smashing Magazine</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2023/03/dynamic-donut-charts-tailwind-css-react/'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>How To Create Dynamic Donut Charts With TailwindCSS And React</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Open-source Repository</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-cloud-api/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-cloud-api</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Social Assets</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1687172044100661248?s=20' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1687172044100661248?s=20</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <CtaExternal href='https://www.cockroachlabs.com/demos/demo-cloud-api/' className='!justify-start my-8'>
            Visit Demo
          </CtaExternal>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='grid gap-0 xl:gap-16 xl:grid-cols-2'>
      <div>
        <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl' id='extra-large-bundle'>
          <a class='no-underline font-black text-brand-salmon' href='#extra-large-bundle'>Extra Large Bundle</a>
        </h2>
        <Image
          width='984'
          height='554'
          alt='Extra Large Bundle'
          src='/images/ia-xl-bundle.jpg'
          class='mt-0 mb-8 border border-brand-outline rounded w-full mx-auto max-w-xl'
        />
        <p>
          Written content with production code publicly available on GitHub and a demo site/application deployed to <span
            class='text-brand-tertiary'>your domain</span
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          Content can be published on either, your company blog, or by a suitable external publisher, with additional
          "how to..." supporting content that mentions, and links back to other assets in the Bundle.
        </p>
        <small
          >Case study: <a href='/demos/2023/05/cockroach-db-data-residency/'
            >The Art of Data Residency and Application Architecture</a
          ></small
        >
      </div>
      <div class='xl:order-2 pt-0 xl:pt-12'>
        <dl>
          <dt>Cockroach Labs Blog</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://www.cockroachlabs.com/blog/multi-region-serverless-data-residency/'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>The Art of Data Residency and Application Architecture</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>The New Stack</dt>
          <dd>
            <a
              href='https://thenewstack.io/tutorial-how-to-create-a-multi-region-node-js-lambda-api/'
              target='_blank'
              rel='noopener'>How to Create a Multi-Region Node.js Lambda API</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Open-source Repositories</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-data-residency/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-data-residency</a
            >
          </dd>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-data-residency-api/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://github.com/cockroachdb/demo-data-residency-api</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <dt>Social Assets</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1682529684032987137?s=20' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1682529684032987137?s=20</a
            >
          </dd>
          <dd>
            <a href='https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1661032283694940161?s=20' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
              >https://x.com/CockroachDB/status/1661032283694940161?s=20</a
            >
          </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
          <CtaExternal href='https://www.cockroachlabs.com/demos/demo-data-residency' className='!justify-start my-8'>
            Visit Demo
          </CtaExternal>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class='my-6 xl:text-4xl text-center'>Sample Vs Production</h2>
      <p class='text-center mx-auto max-w-xl'>
        You may have noticed in the Bundle descriptions I've used the terms; <span class='text-brand-primary'
          >Sample code</span
        > and <span class='text-brand-tertiary'>Production code</span>.
      </p>
      <p class='text-center'>They are different, and here's why.</p>
      <div class='grid gap-8 xl:grid-cols-2 mt-8 mb-4 xl:mt-16 xl:mb-8'>
        <div class='border border-brand-outline bg-brand-surface p-4 sm:p-8 rounded-lg'>
          <h3 class='my-2 xl:text-2xl text-brand-primary'>Sample Code</h3>
          <p>Sample code repositories contain just the code that matters, and are usually quite ugly to look at.</p>
          <p>
            They can be used for <span class='text-brand-primary'>educational purposes</span> but are less suitable for promotional
            purposes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Sample code will be hosted on my personal GitHub account. Links will use a default, "<span
              class='text-brand-primary'>.app</span
            >" URL.
          </p>
          <small class='text-small'>For Example:</small>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a
                href='https://github.com/PaulieScanlon/the-new-stack-astro-react-sprinkling'
                target='_blank'
                rel='noopener'>https://github.com/PaulieScanlon/the-new-stack-astro-react-sprinkling</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href='https://the-new-stack-astro-react-sprinkling.netlify.app/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>
                https://the-new-stack-astro-react-sprinkling.netlify.app</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class='border border-brand-outline bg-brand-surface p-4 sm:p-8 rounded-lg'>
          <h3 class='my-2 xl:text-2xl text-brand-tertiary'>Production Code</h3>
          <p>
            Production code repositories contain all the code that matters <b>plus</b>, everything that makes a demo
            look pretty!
          </p>
          <p>
            They can be used for <span class='text-brand-tertiary'>promotional purposes</span> but are less suitable for
            educational purposes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Production code will be hosted under your company's GitHub account. Links will include <span
              class='text-brand-tertiary'>your domain</span
            > name.
          </p>
          <small class='text-small'>For Example:</small>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a href='https://github.com/neondatabase/ping-thing' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
                >https://github.com/neondatabase/ping-thing</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href='https://neon.tech/demos/ping-thing' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>
                https://neon.tech/demos/ping-thing</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class='text-sm'>
            Deploying a demo to your domain is made possible by using a Proxy Redirect. You can read more about how this
            approach works, here: <a href='/posts/2023/10/what-is-a-proxy-redirect/'>What Is a Proxy Redirect?</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class='text-center mx-auto max-w-3xl'>
        Which route to take will be determined by the project's primary objective. Both have their place in the world
        and I'll work with you to figure out which way to go.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='mb-16'>
      <h2 class='my-6 text-center text-4xl'>Independently Different</h2>
      <div class='mx-auto max-w-2xl'>
        <p class='text-center'>
          Generally speaking, developer content looks like it was created by a Developer, and whilst <span
            class='text-brand-secondary'>Developer Ready</span
          > is fine, <span class='text-brand-tertiary'>Production Ready</span> is better!
        </p>
        <p class='text-center'>If your product or service is aimed at JavaScript developers, we should talk!</p>
      </div>

      <div class='flex justify-center'>
        <ClickToCopyEmail />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Main>
